      "writtenOn": "2017-11-21T21:59:57Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Yeah, it\u0027s a bit stinky. It\u0027s for the test binary bundling and swarming/gtest stuff I think?\n\nFor the gn files, another approach which might be easier is to have a simple empty group in //build/win:default_exe_manifest. This would similar to the stubs we have for UMA, I guess. We\u0027d still need a way to set the `defines` in snapshot/BUILD.gn and test/BUILD.gn (as they\u0027re currently always on, since until now gn \u003d\u003e in-Chromium.)\n\nIn the same vein, maybe we could have a config that\u0027s a no-op in Crashpad //build, but sets defines \u003d [\"CRASHPAD_IN_CHROMIUM\"] when in Chromium... Hmm, I\u0027m liking that better, and then I can entirely drop the goofy //build/dependencies.gni.",
